%% Zennvoi — Auth Flow (sequence)
%% Render: paste into https://mermaid.live → export SVG → save as auth-flow.svg

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant FE as Client App
    participant Auth as Managed Auth Provider
    participant DB as Postgres + RLS
    participant Trig as DB Trigger<br/>(handle_new_user)

    Note over User,DB: --- Signup ---
    User->>FE: Submit {email, password}
    FE->>FE: Reject disposable email domain<br/>(client-side)
    FE->>Auth: signUp(email, password)
    Auth->>DB: Insert auth.users row
    DB->>Trig: Fires on insert
    Trig->>DB: Insert public.profiles row<br/>(id, email, full_name)
    Auth-->>FE: Verification email pending
    Auth->>User: Email with verify link
    User->>Auth: Click verify link → /auth/confirm
    Auth->>DB: Mark email_verified = true

    Note over User,DB: --- Login ---
    User->>FE: Submit credentials
    FE->>Auth: signInWithPassword
    Auth->>DB: Verify hash
    Auth-->>FE: HTTP-only secure cookie
    FE-->>User: Redirect to /dashboard

    Note over User,DB: --- Authenticated DB call (typical read path) ---
    User->>FE: Action (list invoices)
    FE->>DB: select * from documents<br/>(session JWT, anon key)
    DB->>DB: RLS: auth.uid() = user_id
    DB-->>FE: Only own rows
    FE-->>User: Render

    Note over User,DB: --- Privileged action (e.g., create checkout) ---
    User->>FE: Click "Upgrade to Pro"
    FE->>FE: Verify origin allowlist
    FE->>Auth: Get current session
    Auth-->>FE: User object
    FE->>DB: (server-side via API route) call Stripe<br/>service-role re-checks user.id
    DB-->>FE: Checkout URL
    FE-->>User: Redirect to Stripe Checkout
